                                  JVM Architecture
                                  -----------------
Class Loader:
    -> Loads classes into JVM memory
        Class loader does 3 min activities
        1. Loading
        2. Linking
        3. Initialization

        Loading:
        ---------
            Reads .class file.
            Generates binary data.
            saves a set of information inside method area.
                -> Full qualifies name of class and its parent classes
                -> whether class is related to a class, interface or enum.
                -> modifiers, variables, method info will be saved.
        Linking:
        --------
            Verification:
                Ensures bytecdode follows JVM rules and it is safe to execute.          
            Preparation:
                Allocates memory for static variables assign default values.
            Resolution:
                Converts symbollic references to direct reference in memory.
                or Replacing a symbollic name( like variable, method or class names.) with the actual meory address where it exists.
                int 454651423761543 = 10;

        Initialization:
        ---------------
            Static varaibles are assigned with actual values.
            Executes static block.

   class Loader types:
         Bootstrap class loader:
             Loads class that are availabel inside JAVA_HOME/lib
         Extension class loader
              Loads clases from extension directory. JAVA_HOME/lib/ext
         Application class loader
              Loads classes from application class path.
